# Uncomment if you want spikes out of git entirely:
# spikes/

# --- Local Codex scratch ---
.codex

# Spikes are tracked in git (NOTES.md is kept), but spike output files aren't.
spikes/**/__pycache__/
# Smoke-harness per-run state — manifests carry installation_id + GitHub
# review IDs that are useful for reconnaissance; never commit.
spikes/**/*.jsonl
spikes/**/.local/

# Local model-provider exploration spikes (Fireworks/GLM probes) — kept local, EXCEPT the one
# sanitized, recon-free cache-probe result (per-arm cached-token integers + provenance + verdict; no
# secrets, review/installation IDs, or prompt text — enforced by cache_probe.py's exact-key allowlist
# self-test) so the paid decision evidence is reviewable on the branch. Probe SOURCE + wire-capture
# fixtures stay local.
spikes/fireworks/*
!spikes/fireworks/fixtures/
spikes/fireworks/fixtures/*
!spikes/fireworks/fixtures/cache_probe_result.json
spikes/glm/

# OpenAI GPT-5.6 wire-probe capture (openai-native-host arc) — same policy as Fireworks:
# raw wire responses, the manifest, and ESPECIALLY raw billing exports (project/key
# identifiers, financial usage) stay local; the only committable evidence file is the
# operator-authored, exact-key sanitized billing_adjudication.json (response IDs + token
# class counts + window + verdict — no project/org/key identifiers, no dollar amounts).
# Wire-shape regression pinning goes through unit-test fixtures, not by committing raws.
spikes/openai/fixtures/*
!spikes/openai/fixtures/billing_adjudication.json
# refusal-elicitation discovery output (raw model responses to disallowed
# prompts) — never an admission artifact, never committed.
spikes/openai/refusal_discovery_out/

# Arc 2 strict-schema probe output — dry-run measurements + (post-Gate-2) raw
# captures and the run manifest. Same policy as the other probe outputs: the
# evidence stays operator-local; nothing here is a merge input. The DERIVED
# schema is reproducible from source, so there is nothing to preserve in git.
spikes/openai/arc2_out/

